<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Merizocera peraderiya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">A</emphasis>
Endogyne, dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">B</emphasis>
female epigastric area, ventral view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">C</emphasis>
male habitus, dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">D</emphasis>
female habitus, dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">E</emphasis>
female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Female</emphasis>
(paratype). General features and colouration similar to those of male (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Merizocera peraderiya sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443252" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">26D, E</figureCitation>
). Measurements: total length 1.28; carapace 0.61 long, 0.51 wide; abdomen 0.69 long, 0.52 wide. Leg measurements: I 4.25 (1.06, 0.20, 1.28, 1.05, 0.66), II 3.25 (0.83, 0.19, 0.92, 0.80, 0.51), III 2.66 (0.67, 0.17, 0.71, 0.68, 0.43), IV missing. Epigastric area (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Merizocera peraderiya sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443252" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">26B</figureCitation>
): dark brown, patch nearly elliptical. Endogyne (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Merizocera peraderiya sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443252" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">26A</figureCitation>
) with a pair of twisted S-shaped spermathecae, ratio of the width of spermatheca to the interdistance of spermathecae 1:4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
Known only from the type locality (Sri Lanka; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 52" captionStartId="F52" captionText="Figure 52. Distribution records of the new species of Merizocera from Sri Lanka. 1 M. colombo sp. nov. 2 M. galle sp. nov. 3 M. kandy sp. nov. 4 M. kurunegala sp. nov. 5 M. peraderiya sp. nov. 6 M. ratnapura sp. nov. 7 M. salawa sp. nov. 8 M. thenna sp. nov. 9 M. uva sp. nov." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443279" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">52</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
